[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"i am freelance journalist for forbes, business insider and success magazine. I need a website landing page to help the people i am interviewing to understand that to expect and how to prepare for the interview. im mostly doing feel good stories that will appeal to the audience of each respective publication. I want the interview to feel relaxed and comfortable to understand that they will only be shown in an objective neutral light. never anything negative or to hurt their reputation. make a list of disclaimers and FAQs that are common to make the guest comfortable. there is no guarantee of article placement as the final publishing decisions may be up to the respective publication. are including them in the story as someone with a unique background and special story that can inspire others and bring positive awareness of the positive impact or journey they have taken. There is more emphasis on why they are as as personal story and less about their corporation. there should not be any conflict of interest to involve the corporation. there is no direct payment or fee for being included in any article. the interviews are recorded for ease of note taking and confirming quotes. there may be times where claims are included in the final article, the claims must be accompanied by proof before final publishing. make a sample landing page and short video script I can give to each person I interview as they prepare for our story. I will have a google sheet with placeholders like name, article concept, company, . these google sheet sells can be used in any automations to improve organizing a large pipeline of article writing and interviews. lets optimize a a highly informative and comforting landing page and prep kit to give people I am speaking to so they are excited for their interview slot and also feel very prepared Mixture-of-Agents gpt-4.1 Absolutely! Below is a comprehensive, ready-to-use **landing page** for your interviewees. The layout is designed for clarity, comfort, and professionalism, with tactical SOP-level detail. At the end, you'll find a **short video script** and a **process organization table** showing how to use Google Sheets automation in your workflow. --- ## 1. Knowledge Base Document: “Interviewee Experience Prep Kit” **Sections:** 1. Landing Page Copy 2. Disclaimers & FAQs 3. Short Video Script 4. Google Sheet Automation Framework 5. Visual Assets (Infographic/Flowchart) --- ### Section 1: Landing Page Copy --- #### [Logo/Branding: Your Name, Journalist – Forbes, Business Insider, Success] --- #### Welcome! **Thank you for agreeing to share your story. Here’s what you can expect before, during, and after our interview.** --- ##### What This Interview Is: - **A relaxed, feel-good conversation.** - **A chance to spotlight your personal journey.** - **A platform to inspire and inform a wide audience.** --- ##### What This Interview Is NOT: - Investigative or “gotcha” journalism. - A promotional feature about your company. - A paid placement, advertorial, or sponsored content. --- #### What to Expect | Step | What Happens | Your Role | What You Need to Prepare | |---------------------|--------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------| | 1. Pre-Interview | You’ll receive a calendar invite with details. | Confirm your slot and share any preferences. | A quiet space, good connection | | 2. Interview | Relaxed, recorded conversation (20–35 minutes). | Share your personal story, insights, and journey.| Be yourself! No perfect answers | | 3. Post-Interview | We clarify direct quotes and facts by email. | Review if requested, clarify facts if needed. | Proof for any major claims | | 4. Publishing | No guarantee – publication decides final content.| Optional: Share published link with your network.| Celebrate your story! | --- #### FAQs & Disclaimers | FAQ/Disclaimer | Input (What You Provide) | Output (What You Get) | Rationale/Supporting Data | |----------------|-----------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|--------------------------| | Is this for Forbes/BI/Success? | Your story, background, and insights. | Potential feature in one of these publications.| Editorial discretion by publishers. | | Can I review my quotes? | Clarification on direct quotes if requested. | Accurate representation in the piece. | Standard journalism practice. | | Is this paid? | Your time and story. | No fee or payment. | Maintains journalistic integrity. | | Will my company be featured? | Your *personal* journey, not company PR. | Company may be mentioned for context only. | Focus on people, not brands. | | Will it be negative? | Open, honest answers. | Objective, neutral, positive light. | Audience-focused, feel-good stories.| | Will the interview be recorded? | Consent to record (for accuracy, not distribution).| Accurate notes and quotes; recording deleted after use.| Best practice for integrity and fact-checking. | | Can I share the article? | (If published) Link to share with your audience. | Social proof, broader reach. | Win-win for all involved. | | What proof do I need for claims? | Documents, links, or references for notable claims.| Claims only included if verifiable. | Protects everyone’s credibility. | | Do I have to answer every question? | Your comfort level. | You’re always in control. | Builds trust and comfort. | --- #### How to Prepare - **Relax!** This is not a test or business pitch. - **Review your personal milestones and journey.** - **Think about moments that shaped your outlook.** - **Prepare any proof for claims you want included.** - **Let us know if there’s anything you don’t want discussed.** --- #### Next Steps - **Accept your calendar invite:** [Insert Link] - **Fill out the quick prep form:** [Insert Google Form Link] - **Reply with any questions or requests for clarification.** --- #### Contact - **Your Name** - **Email** - **LinkedIn** - **Calendly/Scheduling Link** --- --- ### Section 2: Disclaimers & FAQs (Ready to Copy-Paste) **Disclaimers:** - Interviews are recorded for accuracy but not distributed. - Inclusion in a published article is not guaranteed; final decisions are made by editorial staff. - No direct payment, fee, or compensation for participation. - All claims included in the article must be verifiable with supporting documentation. - The focus is on personal journeys, not corporate promotion. - You may opt out at any time before publication. **FAQs (Condensed):** 1. **Is this a positive story?** Yes – the focus is on inspiration and impact, never exposé or negative angles. 2. **Is this a paid placement?** No – to maintain credibility, features are never paid or sponsored. 3. **Can I review what’s written about me?** We’ll confirm direct quotes and facts, but not full drafts. 4. **Will my company be promoted?** Only for context – the spotlight is on *you*. 5. **Will my interview be recorded?** Yes, for accuracy. Recordings aren’t distributed and are deleted after use. --- --- ### Section 3: Short Video Script --- **[Video, 60-90 seconds, direct to camera, friendly tone]** > Hi, I’m [Your Name], a journalist for Forbes, Business Insider, and Success Magazine. > > I’m excited to share your story with our readers. Here’s what you can expect: > > Our interview is relaxed and informal – I want to hear about your journey, your experiences, and what’s shaped you into who you are today. This isn’t a business pitch or a corporate story – it’s about people, inspiration, and impact. > > There’s no pressure, no “gotcha” questions, and nothing will be used to hurt your reputation. I’m here to put you in a positive, neutral light. > > The interview will be recorded for accuracy, but not shared publicly. If you make any big claims, I’ll just ask for something to back it up – that’s it! > > Please let me know if there’s anything you’re not comfortable discussing, or if you have questions before we start. I look forward to our conversation and sharing your unique journey with the world. > > See you soon! --- --- ### Section 4: Google Sheet Process Automation Table | Step | Google Sheet Field | Input Example | Output/Automation | Rationale/Notes | |-----------------------|---------------------------|--------------------------|---------------------------|---------------------------| | 1. Intake | Name, Email, Article Concept, Company | Jane Doe, janedoe@email.com, “Overcoming Adversity”, Acme Inc. | Auto-generate personalized prep page & video link | Zapier/Make to auto-email invite | | 2. Scheduling | Interview Date/Time | 2025-07-17 2:00pm | Auto-send calendar invite | Integration with Google Calendar | | 3. Prep Form | Prep Form Status | Completed | Notifies you when ready | Google Form/Sheet sync | | 4. Interview | Recording Link | [URL] | Log for reference | Centralized notes | | 5. Follow-up | Quote Confirmation Sent | Yes/No | Auto-reminder if pending | Ensures accuracy | | 6. Publishing | Article Status | Submitted/Published | Auto-notify interviewee | Tracks pipeline | **Tip:** Use [Zapier](https://zapier.com/) or [Make.com](https://www.make.com/) to automate invites, reminders, and follow-ups based on Google Sheet updates. --- --- ### Section 5: Visual Asset (Flowchart) **Interviewee Journey Flowchart** ```mermaid flowchart TD A[Intake: Accept Invite] --> B[Prep: Read FAQ & Watch Video] B --> C[Schedule Interview] C --> D[Interview: Relaxed, Recorded] D --> E[Fact Check: Quote Confirmation] E --> F[Editorial Review (No Guarantee)] F --> G[Publication: Share Link (if published)] ``` --- > **All output and process documentation is stored in the “Interviewee Experience Prep Kit” knowledge base for this chat. As we iterate, I’ll update this doc with any new assets or revisions.** --- ## Next Steps for You 1. **Copy-paste the landing page & FAQ to your site builder (e.g., Carrd, Webflow, Wix).** 2. **Record the short video (use your phone or Loom).** 3. **Set up Google Sheet + Form for intake, and connect with Zapier for automation.** 4. **Link the prep kit page to all pre-interview communications.** 5. **Store and update all new assets in your master “Interviewee Experience Prep Kit” doc.** **Let me know if you want interactive infographics, custom graphics, or a walk-through for any of these steps!** claude-4-sonnet I'll create a comprehensive landing page an Gemini 2.5 Flash As your Chief Marketing Officer and Full-Stack Project Manager, I've evaluated your need for a highly informative and comforting landing page and prep kit for your interviewees. This is not just a logistical tool; it's a critical component of your brand as a journalist, ensuring high-quality interviews, managing expectations, and fostering positive relationships. The goal is to transform the pre-interview anxiety into excitement and preparedness, ultimately leading to more compelling stories and a smoother workflow for you. This approach is rooted in principles of excellent user experience (UX), empathetic communication, and efficient project management, all designed to optimize for a successful \"interview conversion\" – where \"conversion\" means a perfectly prepared, relaxed, and open interviewee. I'm initiating a new knowledge base document for this project, which will house all our outputs, iterations, and strategic decisions related to your interviewee prep process. *** **Knowledge Base Document: Interviewee Prep Kit Project** **Document ID:** IPEPK-20250712-001 **Project Lead:** [Your Name/Journalist] **CMO/PM:** Gemini 2.5 Flash **Date Created:** 2025-07-12 **Status:** Initial Strategy & Design **Objective:** To create a comprehensive, comforting, and highly informative digital prep kit (landing page + video) for interviewees, streamlining the interview process and enhancing interviewee experience. **Key Deliverables for this Phase:** 1. Strategic Overview & Rationale 2. Landing Page Structure & Content (including Disclaimers & FAQs) 3. Short Video Script 4. Detailed Implementation SOP (Table Format) 5. Optimization & Monetization Insights *** **Strategic Overview: Optimizing the Interviewee Journey** Your interviewees are not just subjects; they are collaborators in crafting inspiring narratives. Their comfort and preparedness directly impact the quality of the story you can tell. By providing a structured, empathetic, and transparent pre-interview experience, you are: * **Building Trust:** Addressing potential anxieties upfront, fostering an environment of psychological safety. * **Managing Expectations:** Clearly outlining the process, publication possibilities, and scope of the article, preventing misunderstandings later. * **Enhancing Efficiency:** Reducing time spent on pre-interview clarifications, allowing you to focus on the interview itself. * **Improving Content Quality:** Prepared interviewees provide more articulate, insightful, and relevant information. * **Reinforcing Your Brand:** Positioning yourself as a professional, considerate, and high-integrity journalist. This \"prep kit\" acts as a crucial pre-conversion asset. While you're not selling a product, you are \"selling\" the value of participating in your story. A positive experience here can lead to future referrals, positive testimonials, and strengthen your reputation within your network and with the publications you write for. *** **Landing Page Design & Content Strategy** The landing page will serve as the central hub for all pre-interview information. Its design should be clean, inviting, and easy to navigate, conveying professionalism and warmth. **Overall Philosophy:** The page will adopt a reassuring, transparent, and empowering tone. It should feel like a friendly guide, not a corporate legal document. Visual elements (conceptualized here) will play a key role in breaking down information and enhancing engagement. **Conceptual Interactive Infographics/Visuals:** 1. **\"Your Story Journey\" Flowchart:** A simple, visually appealing flowchart showing the steps from receiving the prep kit to potential article publication. This provides a clear roadmap. * **Visual:** Start with a \"You\" icon -> \"Receive Prep Kit\" -> \"Watch Video & Read Page\" -> \"Interview Day\" -> \"Quote Review\" -> \"Editorial Process\" -> \"Potential Publication.\" * **Rationale:** Visual learners benefit from flowcharts. It demystifies the process, reducing uncertainty. 2. **\"What We Cover vs. What We Don't\" Infographic:** A split screen or two-column graphic clearly delineating personal story focus versus corporate/commercial avoidance. * **Visual:** Left column (green checkmark): \"Personal Journey,\" \"Inspiration,\" \"Lessons Learned,\" \"Impact.\" Right column (red X): \"Company Promotion,\" \"Product Pitches,\" \"Investment Advice,\" \"Controversial Claims without Proof.\" * **Rationale:** Visually reinforces the core message about personal focus and avoids conflict of interest issues. 3. **\"Proof Points\" Iconography:** Small icons next to the section on claims requiring proof, e.g., a document icon, a link icon, a camera icon (for visual proof). * **Rationale:** Makes this important point easily scannable and memorable. **Section Breakdown:** **1. **Hero Section: Welcome & Purpose**** * **Headline:** \"Your Story Matters: Preparing for Your Interview with [Your Name]\" * *Rationale:* Personalized, empowering, and immediately sets a positive tone. * **Sub-headline:** \"Let's craft an inspiring narrative that resonates with readers of Forbes, Business Insider, and Success Magazine.\" * *Rationale:* Establishes credibility and highlights the potential reach. * **Personalized Welcome Message (Dynamically Pulled from Google Sheet):** * \"Hello [Interviewee Name], Thank you for agreeing to share your incredible journey with me for an upcoming article focused on [Article Concept]! I'm so excited to learn more about your unique background and experiences. This page is designed to make you feel completely comfortable and prepared for our conversation.\" * *Rationale:* Personalization immediately builds rapport and shows attention to detail. **2. **About Your Interview: What to Expect**** * **Content:** * **Duration & Format:** \"Our conversation will typically last [e.g., 45-60 minutes] and will be conducted via [Zoom/phone call]. I'll send a calendar invitation with all the details.\" * **Tone & Focus:** \"Expect a relaxed, conversational chat. My aim is to understand *your* personal story—your journey, the challenges you've overcome, the insights you've gained, and the positive impact you've made. We'll explore 'the why' behind your path, focusing on the human elements that inspire others.\" * **Recording:** \"For accuracy and ease of note-taking, our interview will be recorded. This ensures I capture your words precisely and can confirm quotes. The recording is solely for my journalistic purposes and will not be shared publicly.\" * *Rationale:* Sets clear expectations for the interview environment and process, alleviating concerns about being \"on the spot.\" **3. **Preparing for Our Conversation**** * **Content:** * **Find Your Space:** \"Please choose a quiet, well-lit location where you won't be interrupted. If we're on a video call, consider your background.\" * **Technical Check:** \"Ensure you have a stable internet connection or clear phone signal. Test your microphone and camera if using video.\" * **Reflect on Your Journey:** \"Take some time to think about key moments, turning points, or anecdotes that illustrate your story. What valuable lessons have you learned? What message do you hope to convey?\" * **Proof for Claims:** \"If you mention specific claims, statistics, or achievements during our interview, please be prepared to provide supporting documentation or verifiable sources if they are to be included in the final article. This ensures accuracy and journalistic integrity.\" * **Relax!** \"Most importantly, remember this is a conversation, not an interrogation. My goal is to help you shine a positive light on your experiences.\" * *Rationale:* Provides actionable steps, empowering interviewees to prepare effectively and professionally. The \"proof for claims\" point is crucial for journalistic ethics. **4. **Your Comfort & Our Commitment: Key Disclaimers & FAQs**** This section is crucial for managing expectations and building trust through transparency. **Key Disclaimers:** * **No Guarantee of Publication:** \"While I will do my utmost to craft a compelling story, the final decision for article placement rests with the editorial teams of Forbes, Business Insider, or Success Magazine. Factors like editorial calendars, current events, and space availability can influence publishing decisions. There is no guarantee your story will be published.\" * **Objective & Neutral Light:** \"My commitment is to portray you in an objective, neutral, and positive light. The stories I write focus on inspiration and positive impact. There will be no negative portrayal or content intended to harm your reputation.\" * **Personal Story Focus (No Corporate Conflict):** \"The emphasis of this article is on *your personal journey* and *insights*, not on promoting any specific corporation, product, or service. We aim to avoid any perceived conflict of interest, ensuring the story remains genuinely about your unique background and inspiring path. We will not be covering your company's financials, products, or marketing campaigns.\" * **No Payment or Fee:** \"There is no direct payment or fee for being included in any article. Your participation is voluntary, offering an opportunity to share your story and inspire a wide audience.\" * **Interview Recording:** \"As mentioned, interviews are recorded solely for accurate note-taking and precise quote confirmation. These recordings are confidential and for internal use only.\" * **Claim Verification:** \"Any specific claims or factual statements made in the interview that are intended for inclusion in the final article must be accompanied by verifiable proof or sources before publication.\" * **Quote Approval:** \"You will have the opportunity to review and approve your direct quotes before the article is submitted for publication. This ensures accuracy and that your voice is represented authentically.\" * *Rationale:* Clearly states all critical non-negotiables, protecting both the journalist and the interviewee. Formalizing these points in a dedicated section ensures they are not missed. **Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs):** * **Q: Will I get to see the full article before it's published?** * A: You will receive the specific quotes attributed to you for review and approval to ensure accuracy. Due to editorial processes, I cannot provide the full draft of the article for review, but your voice will be accurately represented. * **Q: How long does it take for an article to be published after the interview?** * A: The timeline can vary significantly, from a few weeks to several months, depending on the publication's editorial schedule, my writing deadlines, and the review process. I will keep you updated on its progress. * **Q: What if I say something I later regret or want to clarify?** * A: That's completely normal! Our conversation is informal. If there's something you wish to rephrase or clarify, please let me know during or shortly after the interview. You'll also have the opportunity to review your direct quotes. * **Q: Can I share the article once it's published?** * A: Absolutely! Once published, I encourage you to share the article widely across your networks. It's a great way to amplify your story and its impact. * **Q: What kind of stories are you looking for specifically?** * A: I'm particularly interested in unique personal journeys, stories of resilience, innovation, overcoming challenges, and positive societal impact. The more authentic and inspiring your story, the better! * *Rationale:* Addresses common unspoken anxieties and provides further reassurance, demonstrating empathy. **5. **About Your Journalist: [Your Name]**** * **Content:** * \"Hi, I'm [Your Name]! As a freelance journalist for Forbes, Business Insider, and Success Magazine, I have a passion for uncovering and sharing inspiring stories of individuals who are making a difference. My work focuses on positive narratives that empower and motivate our readers. I believe everyone has a unique story, and I'm honored to help you share yours.\" * **Photo:** A professional, friendly headshot of you. * *Rationale:* Personalizes the experience, builds credibility, and establishes rapport. People like to know who they are speaking with. **6. **Ready to Shine? Confirm Your Interview!**** * **Call to Action:** \"We're excited to hear your story! Please click the button below to confirm your interview time and add it to your calendar.\" * **Button:** \"[Confirm My Interview Time]\" (Link to Calendly or similar scheduling tool) * *Rationale:* Clear, simple call to action to move the interviewee to the next step. *** **Short Video Script: \"A Personal Welcome & Quick Guide\"** This video should be concise (1-2 minutes), friendly, and professional. It's designed to add a human touch and reinforce the key messages of comfort and preparation. You should be on camera, smiling, and speaking directly to the viewer. **Video Title:** Welcome to Your Interview Prep! ``` [Visual: You, smiling, in a professional but warm setting. Perhaps a subtle background with books or a clean office. Soft, inviting music starts and fades.] **(0-5 seconds) Introduction & Warm Welcome:** \"Hi there, I'm [Your Name], and I'm so excited to connect with you! Thank you for agreeing to share your inspiring story with me for an upcoming feature in [mention one or two relevant publications, e.g., Forbes or Business Insider].\" **(5-20 seconds) Purpose & Tone:** \"My goal is to bring your unique journey to life for our readers – focusing on your personal insights, the challenges you've overcome, and the positive impact you've made. Think of our interview as a relaxed, friendly conversation, not a formal interrogation. I'm genuinely interested in *your* story.\" **(20-40 seconds) What to Expect & Reassurance:** \"This video, along with the detailed information on this page, is designed to make you feel completely comfortable and prepared. We'll chat for about [e.g., 45-60 minutes], and the conversation will be recorded solely for my note-taking and to ensure I capture your words accurately. Rest assured, my focus is always to portray you in a positive, objective, and inspiring light. Your reputation and story are safe with me.\" **(40-55 seconds) Quick Prep Tips & Call to Action:** \"On this page, you'll find everything you need: simple tips on how to prepare, what kind of questions we'll explore, and answers to common questions about the process. Please take a few moments to review it. It will help us make the most of our time together.\" **(55-60 seconds) Closing & Excitement:** \"I truly believe your story has the power to inspire many, and I can't wait to hear it. If you have any immediate questions, feel free to reach out. Otherwise, I look forward to our conversation!\" [Visual: Your name and website/contact info briefly appear on screen. Music swells slightly and fades out.] ``` * **Rationale:** A short video personalizes the experience, builds immediate trust through visual presence, and quickly conveys the core message of comfort and positive intent. It's a highly effective way to engage busy individuals. *** **Automation & Workflow Integration** Leveraging your Google Sheet with placeholders is a brilliant move for efficiency and personalization. * **Google Sheet Structure:** * Column A: `Interviewee Name` * Column B: `Interviewee Email` * Column C: `Article Concept` * Column D: `Company (for reference, not article focus)` * Column E: `Personalized Landing Page Link` (This column will be populated by automation) * Column F: `Interview Date/Time` * Column G: `Interview Status` (e.g., \"Prep Kit Sent,\" \"Interview Scheduled,\" \"Interview Completed,\" \"Quotes Sent,\" \"Article Submitted,\" \"Published\") * **Automation Flow (Conceptual):** 1. **Trigger:** When you add a new row to the Google Sheet with `Interviewee Name`, `Interviewee Email`, and `Article Concept`. 2. **Action 1 (Generate Personalized Link):** Use a tool like Zapier or Make.com (formerly Integromat) to create a unique URL for the landing page. This URL would have parameters that dynamically populate the `[Interviewee Name]` and `[Article Concept]` fields on the landing page. * Example: `yourdomain.com/interview-prep?name=[Interviewee Name]&concept=[Article Concept]` * *Note:* This requires your landing page to be built on a platform that supports URL parameters (e.g., WordPress with a page builder, custom HTML/JS, or a dedicated landing page builder like Leadpages, Unbounce, or ClickFunnels). 3. **Action 2 (Populate Google Sheet):** The generated personalized URL is automatically written back into the `Personalized Landing Page Link` column in your Google Sheet. 4. **Action 3 (Send Personalized Email):** An automated email (using Gmail integration via Zapier/Make.com or an email marketing platform like MailerLite/ActiveCampaign) is sent to the `Interviewee Email`. * **Email Subject:** \"Your Interview Prep Kit with [Your Name] for the [Article Concept] Story!\" * **Email Body:** \"Hi [Interviewee Name], I'm looking forward to our upcoming interview for an inspiring story about [Article Concept]! To help you prepare and feel completely comfortable, I've put together a special Interview Prep Kit just for you. It includes everything you need to know about what to expect, how to prepare, and answers to common questions. Please click here to access your personalized kit: [Personalized Landing Page Link] You'll also find a short welcome video from me on the page. Looking forward to our conversation! Best, [Your Name]\" 5. **Action 4 (Update Status):** The `Interview Status` in the Google Sheet is automatically updated to \"Prep Kit Sent.\" * **Rationale:** This automation significantly reduces manual work, ensures consistent delivery of the prep kit, and provides a highly personalized experience, reinforcing professionalism and care. It also creates a clear audit trail of your outreach. *** **Implementation SOP: Interviewee Prep Kit Deployment** This detailed, click-by-click SOP outlines the steps to set up and utilize your new interviewee prep system. | **Step** | **Action Item** | **Description** | **Expected Input** | **Expected Output** | **Rationale/Optimization** | | :------- | :-------------- | :-------------- | :----------------- | :------------------ | :------------------------ | | **Phase 1: Foundation Setup** | | | | | | | 1 | **Choose Landing Page Platform** | Select a platform for hosting your landing page. Options include dedicated landing page builders (Leadpages, Unbounce), website builders (Webflow, Squarespace), or WordPress with a page builder (Elementor, Divi). | Decision on preferred platform based on ease of use, cost, and customization needs. | Chosen platform account set up and ready. | Optimizes for ease of design and future scalability. User-friendly platforms reduce development time. | | 2 | **Design Landing Page Template** | Implement the conceptual landing page design outlined above. Ensure all sections, disclaimers, and FAQs are clearly presented. | Landing page content (text, your photo), chosen platform. | A fully designed, but unpopulated, landing page template on your chosen platform. | Creates a professional, consistent brand experience. A template allows for rapid deployment for each interviewee. | | 3 | **Integrate Dynamic Content** | Configure the landing page to accept URL parameters (e.g., `?name=John%20Doe&concept=Resilience`) to dynamically populate the `[Interviewee Name]` and `[Article Concept]` fields. | Platform's dynamic content features (e.g., custom fields, URL parameter integration). | Landing page fields (`[Interviewee Name]`, `[Article Concept]`) automaticall"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=08339d35-caed-46ee-b573-2a510d272cbd","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=08339d35-caed-46ee-b573-2a510d272cbd"}]}]}]
